  "prompt": "What is meaning of impeachment?",
  "response": "Impeachment is a formal process by which a legislative body brings charges against a high-ranking government official, such as a president, vice president, or other civil officer, for alleged misconduct. The key points about impeachment are:\n\n1. It is a political process, not a criminal trial\n\n2. It typically involves two main steps:\n- Formal accusation of misconduct\n- Potential removal from office\n\n3. Grounds for impeachment can include:\n- Treason\n- Bribery\n- Other serious \"high crimes and misdemeanors\"\n\n4. In the United States, the House of Representatives has the power to impeach, and the Senate conducts the trial\n\n5. A successful impeachment requires:\n- Majority vote in the House to impeach\n- Two-thirds majority vote in the Senate to convict and remove from office\n\n6. Being impeached does not necessarily mean automatic removal from office\n\n7. It is a way to hold powerful government officials accountable for serious misconduct\n\nThe primary purpose of impeachment is to provide a constitutional mechanism for removing officials who have abused their power or committed serious offenses that undermine their ability to serve effectively.",
